fileChanges.details:
Move the .top-gradient rendering rules from colors.css into this file. Use the generic --gradient-left, --gradient-right, and --accent-color variables. Content:

/* Hero gradient system - uses generic --gradient-left/--gradient-right from colors.css */
.top-gradient {
	position: absolute;
	top: 0;
	left: 0;
	width: 100%;
	height: 150vw;
	z-index: -10;
	background:
		linear-gradient(180deg, color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 60%, transparent) 25%, color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-off-white) 60%, transparent) 80%, transparent),
		radial-gradient(ellipse 30% 44% at 20% 45%, var(--gradient-left), transparent),
		radial-gradient(ellipse 44% 33% at 80% 30%, var(--gradient-right), transparent);
}

Rationale: Replaced --gradient-main with --accent-color (always identical). Replaced --gradient-circle-left/--gradient-circle-right with --gradient-left/--gradient-right from the generic system. Eliminated ALL per-color .hero.X overrides since the generic system in colors.css already sets --gradient-left and --gradient-right per accent color. Uses vanilla CSS per block-specific CSS convention.

